<ext_description linkend="characteristic_mim">
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: characteristic_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.characteristic_type">
A <b>characteristic_type</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> that specifies a boolean property, a numeric property whose units are in accordance with ISO 10303-41, a compound characteristic, a
logical property, a string property, or an externally defined property for a characteristic.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: coordinated_representation_item
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item">
<p>
A <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> and a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/>
that implements the ARM concepts of:
</p><ul>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Plus_minus_tolerance_characteristic"/>;</li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Statistical_tolerance_characteristic"/>;</li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Symmetrical_tolerance_characteristic"/>;</li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Tolerance_characteristic"/>.</li>
</ul>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: parameter_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.parameter_type">
<p>
A <b>parameter_type</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> that specifies a boolean property type, a
logical property type, a physical property type or a string property type
for a <express_ref linkend="Model_parameter:mim:Model_parameter_mim.model_parameter"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: table_representation_item
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.table_representation_item">
A <b>table_representation_item</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.compound_representation_item"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.table_representation_item.wr:WR1">
the <b>table_representation_item</b> shall be refered by at least one <express_ref linkend="Group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment"/>
as a member of <express_ref linkend="Group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment.items"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.table_representation_item.wr:WR2">
the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.compound_representation_item.item_element"/>
inherited from <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.compound_representation_item"/>
shall be <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.list_representation_item"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: range_characteristic
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.range_characteristic">
	A <b>range_characteristic</b> is a type of
	<express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> 
	and of
	<express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/>.
</ext_description>


</ext_descriptions>
